   - Replaced hardcoded 60px with CSS variable --ob-chrome-height (default
     60px) in .sidebar-layout height/max-height and .sidebar-content
     max-height.
   - Replaced hardcoded 100px with --ob-chrome-height-ro in read-only mode
     overrides.

2. src/front/static/global/js/breadcrumb.js
   - Added _updateChromeHeight() method: measures the breadcrumb's actual
     offsetHeight after it becomes visible and sets --ob-chrome-height and
     --ob-chrome-height-ro on :root so the sidebar layout subtracts the
     correct total chrome height.
   - Called immediately after nav.classList.remove('d-none').

