================================================================================
Prevent FAB/popup from overlapping the right detail panel
================================================================================
Context: The assistant FAB and popup are absolutely positioned inside the
card-body. When the right detail panel opens (entity/relationship editing),
it occupies the right side of the canvas but the FAB stayed at a fixed
right: 20px, overlapping the panel.

Changes:
1. src/front/static/ontology/css/ontology-assistant.css
   - Both .assistant-fab and .assistant-popup now use
     right: calc(Npx + var(--ob-panel-offset, 0px)) instead of a fixed
     right value, so they shift left when the panel is open.
   - Added transition on `right` for smooth sliding.

2. src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-assistant.js
   - Added initPanelOffsetWatcher() function that:
     a) Uses a MutationObserver on #ontology-map-container to detect
        the panel-open class being toggled.
     b) Uses a second MutationObserver (childList) to detect when the
        .shared-detail-panel element is first created, then attaches
        a ResizeObserver to track user-driven resize via the drag handle.
     c) On each change, reads the panel's offsetWidth + resize handle
        width and sets --ob-panel-offset on the .card-body element.
   - Called from DOMContentLoaded alongside existing event bindings.

