================================================================================
Fix assistant blocking the event loop (UI freezes during chat)
================================================================================
Context: The /ontology/assistant/chat endpoint was declared as `async def` but
called the synchronous run_agent() function directly. Since run_agent() performs
multiple blocking HTTP calls to the LLM serving endpoint (up to 20 iterations,
each with a 120s timeout), this blocked the single-threaded asyncio event loop.
While the assistant was processing, no other HTTP request could be served,
causing the rest of the UI (right panel, API calls) to appear frozen.

Changes:
1. src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py
   - Added `import asyncio` at the top of the module.
   - Wrapped the `run_assistant(...)` call inside `await asyncio.to_thread()`
     so it executes in a background thread pool, freeing the event loop to
     serve other concurrent requests while the LLM agent is running.

Modified files:
- src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py

